article.description: Andre Walker scored a career-high 31 points, including the winning free throws with four seconds left, and Loyola-Maryland defeated Army 100-99 in double overtime Saturday.
article.headline: Loyola (Md.) beats Army in double OT 100-99
article.linkText: Loyola (Md.) beats Army in double OT 100-99
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- Andre Walker scored a career-high 31 points, including the winning free throws with four seconds left, and Loyola-Maryland defeated Army 100-99 in double overtime Saturday. Dylan Cox, whose 3-pointer with 1.6 seconds left in regulation tied the game, made two free throws to give Army the lead with 12 seconds remaining in the second overtime. But he fouled Walker who made both free throws before Army's Tanner Plomb missed a 27-footer at the buzzer. Army had a chance to win in the first overtime when Kyle Wilson missed a layup and Mac Hoffman's two putbacks wouldn't fall. Jarred Jones matched a career high with 28 points for the Greyhounds (8-15, 7-5 Patriot). Plomb scored 25 points for the Black Knights (3-11, 4-8) but was just 3 of 15 from the arc. Wilson added 22 points, Cox 17 points and 10 rebounds and Kevin Ferguson 17 points and 14 boards.
